eCount": 12, "uploadedAt": "2026-02-13T07:50:14.532Z", "expiresAt": "2026-02-15T07:50:10.392Z"}], "feedback": [{"versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "score": 3, "strengths": ["Uses concrete, engaging case studies (jazz, Renaissance art, blood-letting, Human Genome Project) to illustrate shifts in validation of knowledge", "Gestures toward multiple perspectives, including non-Western views, showing an attempt to widen the discussion beyond a single cultural framework"], "weaknesses": ["Discussion remains largely descriptive with limited analytical engagement with TOK concepts such as justification, methodology or evidence", "The prescribed title\u00e2\u0080\u0099s key terms (e.g. \u00e2\u0080\u009cfragility\u00e2\u0080\u009d) and an explicit knowledge question are only intermittently signposted, weakening focus", "Arguments are underdeveloped and supported by unsupported assertions rather than clear, coherent reasoning", "Transitions between areas of knowledge (arts to natural sciences) are abrupt and lack synthesis to show comparative insight", "Counter-claims and implications are mentioned but not evaluated or integrated into a sustained discussion"], "calculationMethod": "Holistic AI evaluation: The strand assessment places the essay in the 3\u00e2\u0080\u00934 band for Criterion A at its lower end (score 3), reflecting a basic connection to the title with relevant examples but predominantly descriptive treatment and limited argumentation. The work demonstrates strength in concrete case studies and an initial attempt at multiple perspectives, yet it consistently fails to develop clear, coherent analysis or to integrate TOK terminology and knowledge questions. Given the official total mark of 3 and the predominance of weaknesses in analytical depth and coherence, awarding 3 marks accurately reflects the quality distribution against the rubric.", "groupName": "TOK Essay"}], "strandSelections": [{"versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "strandId": "8dc05406-c8b4-4575-8c75-4290cad64660", "selectedBandId": "d4162f84-b125-401d-a926-d829eb4f30f0", "bandScore": 3, "reasoning": "$49"}], "annotations": [{"id": "625d5a0e-a4a2-4512-82f5-55a2fee13b1f", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.5539, "width": 0.7120000000000001, "height": 0.3499000000000001}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.5539}, {"x": 0.8887, "y": 0.5539}, {"x": 0.8887, "y": 0.9038}, {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.9038}], "comment": "This paragraph presents a descriptive account of jazz\u00e2\u0080\u0099s social reception, but it lacks development of how subjectivity in the arts constitutes an intrinsic fragility of revered knowledge. Integrate explicit TOK concepts (e.g., justification or shared versus personal knowledge).", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "578471fb-6832-48bf-8a3b-9239905fb0e2", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 4, "bbox": {"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.0877, "width": 0.705, "height": 0.5833}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8805, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8805, "y": 0.671}, {"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.671}], "comment": "This extensive historical overview of Renaissance art is descriptive but does not analyse how its techniques or institutional support mitigate or expose fragility. Introduce evaluation of how social and cultural contexts continue to challenge its revered status.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "06ac3eb1-3f66-40ed-bb71-8a98ee21d881", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 4, "bbox": {"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.7199, "width": 0.6962, "height": 0.18390000000000006}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.7199}, {"x": 0.8717, "y": 0.7199}, {"x": 0.8717, "y": 0.9038}, {"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.9038}], "comment": "The mention of non-Western perspectives is promising but remains undeveloped. Expand this point by evaluating specific examples of cultural divergence to demonstrate that Renaissance art\u00e2\u0080\u0099s reverence is not universally sustained.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "4b606a98-d8d5-47ae-bac2-fe8646a04bc0", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 2, "bbox": {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.0877, "width": 0.7120000000000001, "height": 0.4172}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8887, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8887, "y": 0.5049}, {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.5049}], "comment": "The introduction outlines the structure but does not explicitly formulate a knowledge question or link the prescribed title\u00e2\u0080\u0099s terminology to TOK concepts. Consider signposting the key question and defining terms like \u00e2\u0080\u009cfragility\u00e2\u0080\u009d to sharpen the analytical focus.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "d1a22639-a20b-4113-bdf6-9e7e2820326b", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "strength", "pageNumber": 3, "bbox": {"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.0877, "width": 0.71, "height": 0.6839}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.7716}, {"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.7716}], "comment": "The historical narrative of jazz, including shifts from rejection to institutional recognition, is engaging and grounded in concrete examples, providing a clear case study for exploring knowledge validation in the arts.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "c4f39210-8014-4982-8a9a-bf7042d314b2", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 3, "bbox": {"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.8179, "width": 0.71, "height": 0.08590000000000009}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.8179}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.8179}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.9038}, {"x": 0.1755, "y": 0.9038}], "comment": "The transition to Renaissance art is stated but incomplete and lacks clarity. Refine the topic sentence to establish why Renaissance art serves as a contrasting case for resilience and connect it back to the fragility theme.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "b1182bc7-748e-4bf0-82c4-d4b373ca81f5", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 5, "bbox": {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.0877, "width": 0.7088, "height": 0.3851}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.4728}, {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.4728}], "comment": "The shift from arts to natural sciences is abrupt and lacks synthesis. Strengthen the link by comparing validation mechanisms in both areas of knowledge and explaining their roles in exposing or reinforcing fragility.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "f591b139-f09a-4ce5-aff5-99f365d41643", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 5, "bbox": {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.5196, "width": 0.7057, "height": 0.3842000000000001}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.5196}, {"x": 0.8824, "y": 0.5196}, {"x": 0.8824, "y": 0.9038}, {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.9038}], "comment": "The bloodletting case is well contextualized historically but needs deeper analysis of how its lack of empirical methodology illustrates fragility in scientific knowledge and challenges assumptions of objectivity.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "fa70c69a-a456-44f7-8c22-81be0cf1513b", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 6, "bbox": {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.0877, "width": 0.7088, "height": 0.3843}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.0877}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.472}, {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.472}], "comment": "Reference to Kuhn\u00e2\u0080\u0099s paradigm shifts is apt, yet the essay does not fully tie this theory back to the central claim. Elaborate on how paradigm shifts serve as systematic evidence of the fragility of once-revered scientific theories.", "color": null, "status": "unread", "statusUpdatedAt": null, "statusUpdatedBy": null, "groupName": "TOK Essay"}, {"id": "3fb74aae-6344-459a-badf-57881f9e3103", "versionId": "5bd6927b-5684-4dd7-bc93-380c2cf0c019", "criterionId": "e708a9f2-1aa2-48b1-8848-2655ed338b08", "strandId": null, "type": "weakness", "pageNumber": 6, "bbox": {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.5196, "width": 0.7088, "height": 0.3842000000000001}, "polygon": [{"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.5196}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.5196}, {"x": 0.8855, "y": 0.9038}, {"x": 0.1767, "y": 0.9038}], "comment": "The Human Genome Project example is descriptive of success but lacks critical evaluation of its limitations or potential challenges. Discuss aspects like ethical debates or evolving technologies to assess its resilience more robustly.", "color": null, "sta